"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/993730","Department for Exiting the European Union ","false","2018-10-30","<p>In the Joint Report of December 2017, the EU and UK agreed the need for provisions in the Withdrawal Agreement preventing a hard border between Northern Ireland and Ireland. As the Prime Minister said during her Statement to the House on 22nd October 2018, we do not want to extend the implementation period, nor do we believe that extending it will be necessary. We are working at pace to ensure that the necessary arrangements for our future partnership are in place for 31 December 2020.</p>","Daventry","Chris Heaton-Harris",,"2018-10-30T13:26:44.65Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/993730/answer","Biography information for Chris Heaton-Harris","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/993730/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/993730/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union ","Exiting the European Union ","2018-10-23","Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, pursuant to the Answer of 23 October to Question 179064 on Brexit, whether the Government has made an assessment of the steps required to extend the transition period in the event that the arrangements for a future partnership between the UK and the EU are not in place.","false","Biography information for Tom Brake","Carshalton and Wallington","Tom Brake","182666"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/993731","Department for Exiting the European Union ","false","2018-10-26","<p>The Government’s policy remains that Article 50 will not be extended. We will be leaving the EU on 29 March 2019 and are negotiating to that timeline. We are confident of reaching a deal which is in the best interests of both the UK and the EU.</p><p> </p>","Daventry","Chris Heaton-Harris",,"2018-10-26T08:07:11.98Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/993731/answer","Biography information for Chris Heaton-Harris","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/993731/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/993731/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union ","Exiting the European Union ","2018-10-23","Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, pursuant to the Answer of 17 October to Question 175802 on Brexit, whether the Government has held any discussions with EU member states on the potential extension of Article 50.","false","Biography information for Tom Brake","Carshalton and Wallington","Tom Brake","182667"
