"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/993741","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-10-29","<p>The UK is supportive of proposals for Marine Protected Areas (MPAs) in the Weddell Sea and East Antarctica, both of which are being presented at the meeting of the Commission for the Conservation of Antarctic Marine Living Resources (CCAMLR) currently taking place and due to conclude on the 2 November 2018. UK scientists and experts have been closely involved in the development of the Weddell Sea proposals. Foreign Office officials have also been lobbying other members of CCAMLR in favour of the proposals.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan","182866 ; 182867 ; 182868","2018-10-29T15:56:00.13Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/993741/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/993741/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/993741/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-10-23","Antarctic: Marine Protected Areas","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what steps he has taken to secure the adoption of a marine sanctuary in the Weddell Sea.","false","Biography information for Stephen Gethins","North East Fife","Stephen Gethins","182865"
