bout Schools’ links data, but which includes those that have resulted from local re-organisation of school provision.</p><p>The table also reflects schools that have subsequently closed.</p><p>For ‘type of establishment’, we have included all academies and maintained schools, including special schools, pupil referral units, alternative provision and 16 to 19 provision.</p>",,"Lord Agnew of Oulton",,"2018-11-01T16:34:40.65Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/993830/answer","Biography information for Lord Agnew of Oulton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/993830/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/993830/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-10-23","Schools: Construction","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government how many new faith schools were built in each of the years 2010 to 2017; and how many non faith schools were built in the same period.","false","Biography information for Lord Storey",,"Lord Storey","HL10963"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/993831","Cabinet Office","false","2018-11-01","<p>The Government does not comment on individual honours nominations. Due to the confidential nature of the honours system, discretion regarding individual cases is considered important to safeguard the confidentiality and integrity of the honours system.</p><p> </p><p>Nominations are considered by one of ten independent Honours Committees before recommendations are made to Her Majesty The Queen.</p>",,"Lord Young of Cookham",,"2018-11-01T12:37:56.22Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/993831/answer","Biography information for Lord Young of Cookham","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/993831/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/993831/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2018-10-23","Alastair Cook","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government what consideration they have given to recomending Alastair Cook for knighthood.","false","Biography information for Lord Tyrie",,"Lord Tyrie","HL10964"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/993832","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-11-06","<p>With the aim of improving the lives of all those affected by a rare disease, the United Kingdom Government published <em>The UK Strategy for Rare Diseases</em> in 2013, a high-level framework containing 51 commitments which sets out a seven-year strategic vision from 2013-2020. A copy of the Strategy is attached. The Government is committed to implementing the Strategy’s commitments and has, in January 2018, published two implementation plans setting out its actions for England. Copies of the Department’s <em>The UK Strategy for Rare Diseases: Rare Diseases implementation plan for England</em> and NHS England’s <em>Implementation Plan for the UK Strategy for Rare Diseases</em> are attached.</p><p>The Government has not made any assessment of differences in access to medicines for the treatment of rare diseases or on the available number of treatments between England, the devolved administrations and economically similar countries in Europe.</p><p>With regard to the Government’s assessment of the sustainability of the National Institute for Health and Care Excellence’s (NICE) appraisal process for rare disease medicines that do not meet the highly specialised technology criteria, patients with rare diseases in England benefit from the same NHS Constitution right to clinically and cost-effective medicines as patients with more common conditions. NICE has recommended a number of medicines for the treatment of rare diseases through its technology appraisal and highly specialised technology evaluation programmes which are now routinely available to National Health Service patients in line with NICE’s recommendations.</p>",,"Lord O'Shaughnessy","HL10966 ; HL10967 ; HL10968","2018-11-06T13:06:10.223Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/993832/answer","Biography information for Lord O'Shaughnessy","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/993832/answer","UK_Strategy_for_Rare_Diseases.pdf ; UK_strategy_for_rare_diseases_-_implementation_plan_for_England.pdf ; NHSE implementation-plan-uk-strategy-for-rare-diseases.pdf","UK_Strategy_for_Rare_Diseases.pdf ; UK_strategy_for_rare_diseases_-_implementation_plan_for_England.pdf ; NHSE implementation-plan-uk-strategy-for-rare-diseases.pdf","The UK Strategy for Rare Diseases ; UK Strategy for Rare Diseases Implementation Plan ; NHS England Rare Diseases Implementation Plan","The UK Strategy for Rare Diseases ; UK Strategy for Rare Diseases Implementation Plan ; NHS England Rare Diseases Implementation Plan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/993832/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-10-23","Rare Diseases: Drugs","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government what steps they are taking to reduce any disparity in access to rare disease medicines between England, Wales, Scotland and Northern Ireland.","false","Biography information for Viscount Waverley",,"Viscount Waverley","HL10965"
