"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/992754","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-10-31","<p>This information is available in the published Court Outcomes by Police Force Area data tool: <a href="https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/733996/court-outcomes-by-pfa-2017-update.xlsx" target="_blank">https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/733996/court-outcomes-by-pfa-2017-update.xlsx</a></p><p> </p><p>To limit the data to Wales, drag ‘Police Force Area’ field into the ‘Filters’ area and select Dyfed-Powys, Gwent, North Wales and South Wales.</p><p> </p><p>For the number of prosecutions, filter the data using the ‘Court Type’ field to ’02: Magistrates Court’.</p>","South East Cambridgeshire","Lucy Frazer",,"2018-10-31T15:05:40.957Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/992754/answer","Biography information for Lucy Frazer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/992754/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/992754/answer","South East Cambridgeshire","Lucy Frazer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/992754/answer/previousversion/81910","Biography information for Lucy Frazer","54","Justice","Justice","2018-10-22","Prosecutions: Wales","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what estimate he has made of the number of defendants who have had legal proceedings brought against them in Wales in each year from 2013 and 2017.","false","Biography information for Liz Saville Roberts","Dwyfor Meirionnydd","Liz Saville Roberts","182269"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/992755","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-10-31","<table><tbody><tr><td><p>This information is available in the published Court Outcomes by Police Force Area data tool: <a href="https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/733996/court-outcomes-by-pfa-2017-update.xlsx" target="_blank">https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/733996/court-outcomes-by-pfa-2017-update.xlsx</a>. To limit the data to Wales, drag ‘Police Force Area’ field into the ‘Filters’ area and select Dyfed-Powys, Gwent, North Wales and South Wales. To see the number of prosecutions for indictable offences, drag the ‘Offence Type’ field into rows and sum the amounts for ’01: Indictable only’ and ’02: Triable Either Way’. Please note that all cases are first heard at Magistrates Court and more serious cases are sent for trial or sentencing at Crown Court, therefore some cases may be counted twice within a given year – once at Magistrates and then again at Crown Court.</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p>","South East Cambridgeshire","Lucy Frazer",,"2018-10-31T14:58:28.417Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/992755/answer","Biography information for Lucy Frazer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/992755/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/992755/answer","South East Cambridgeshire","Lucy Frazer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/992755/answer/previousversion/81911","Biography information for Lucy Frazer","54","Justice","Justice","2018-10-22","Prosecutions: Wales","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what estimate he has made of the number of defendants who were prosecuted for indictable offences in Wales in each year from 2013 and 2017.","false","Biography information for Liz Saville Roberts","Dwyfor Meirionnydd","Liz Saville Roberts","182270"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/992756","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-10-31","<p>This information is available in the published out of court disposals data tool: <a href="https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/733984/out-of-court-disposals-tool-2017-update.xlsx" target="_blank">https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/733984/out-of-court-disposals-tool-2017-update.xlsx</a></p><p> </p><p>To limit the data to Wales, filter the data using Police Force Area and select Dyfed-Powys, Gwent, North Wales and South Wales.</p><p> </p><p>For Penalty Notice for Disorders (PND) open the PND pivot table and limit the data to Wales. For each year, the grand total gives the number of PNDs issued.</p><p> </p><p>For cautions, open the Cautions pivot table and limit the data to Wales. For each year, the grand total gives the number of cautions issued.</p><p>The proportions of different out of courts disposals cannot be produced, as data is only available for (b) PNDs, (c) cautions for indictable offences and (e) cautions for summary non-motoring offences. Open the Cautions pivot table, split the data by offence type, drag the ‘offence type’ variable from the filters box into the rows box (clear any variables that were already in the rows box). For each year, sum the number of cautions for indictable only and triable either way to get the number of cautions for indictable offences.</p>","South East Cambridgeshire","Lucy Frazer",,"2018-10-31T14:56:09.927Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/992756/answer","Biography information for Lucy Frazer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/992756/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/992756/answer","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/992756/answer/previousversion/81948","Biography information for Rory Stewart","54","Justice","Justice","2018-10-22","Alternatives to Prison: Wales","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many out of court disposals were issued in Wales in each year from 2013 and 2017.","false","Biography information for Liz Saville Roberts","Dwyfor Meirionnydd","Liz Saville Roberts","182271"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/992757","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-10-31","<p>This information is available in the published out of court disposals data tool: <a href="https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/733984/out-of-court-disposals-tool-2017-update.xlsx" target="_blank">https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/733984/out-of-court-disposals-tool-2017-update.xlsx</a></p><p> </p><p>To limit the data to Wales, filter the data using Police Force Area and select Dyfed-Powys, Gwent, North Wales and South Wales.</p><p> </p><p>For Penalty Notice for Disorders (PND) open the PND pivot table and limit the data to Wales. For each year, the grand total gives the number of PNDs issued.</p><p> </p><p>For cautions, open the Cautions pivot table and limit the data to Wales. For each year, the grand total gives the number of cautions issued.</p><p>The proportions of different out of courts disposals cannot be produced, as data is only available for (b) PNDs, (c) cautions for indictable offences and (e) cautions for summary non-motoring offences. Open the Cautions pivot table, split the data by offence type, drag the ‘offence type’ variable from the filters box into the rows box (clear any variables that were already in the rows box). For each year, sum the number of cautions for indictable only and triable either way to get the number of cautions for indictable offences.</p>","South East Cambridgeshire","Lucy Frazer",,"2018-10-31T14:56:31.533Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/992757/answer","Biography information for Lucy Frazer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/992757/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/992757/answer","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/992757/answer/previousversion/81946","Biography information for Rory Stewart","54","Justice","Justice","2018-10-22","Alternatives to Prison: Wales","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many and what proportion of out of court disposals issued in Wales were in relation to (a) Community Resolutions, (b) Penalty Notices for Disorder, (c) cautions for indictable offences, (d) cannabis and khat warnings and (e) cautions for summary non-motoring offences in each year between 2013 and 2017.","false","Biography information for Liz Saville Roberts","Dwyfor Meirionnydd","Liz Saville Roberts","182272"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/992758","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-10-30","<p>This information is available in the published out of court disposals data tool: <a href="https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/733984/out-of-court-disposals-tool-2017-update.xlsx" target="_blank">https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/733984/out-of-court-disposals-tool-2017-update.xlsx</a></p><p> </p><p>To limit the data to Wales, filter the data using Police Force Area and select Dyfed-Powys, Gwent, North Wales and South Wales.</p><p> </p><p>For the number of Penalty Notices for Disorder (PND) issued for each tier of offence open the PND pivot table, limit the data to Wales, remove the variables from the rows box and drag the ‘Offence’ variable from the filters box into the rows box. For the total number of lower tier offences, in the ‘Offence’ filter, select all the offences that begin with DB. For the total number of higher tier offences, repeat as above, selecting all offences beginning with DA.</p><p> </p><p>For the proportion of people who paid their PND in full, open the PND pivot table, limit the data to Wales and ensure the ‘Outcomes’ variable is in the rows box. For each year, sum the numbers for ‘paid in full - timing unknown’ and divide this number by the total PNDs issued (grand total).</p><p> </p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart","182274","2018-10-30T17:38:46.087Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/992758/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/992758/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/992758/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-10-22","Fixed Penalties: Wales","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many Penalty Notices for Disorder were issued for each tier of offence in Wales in each year between 2013 and 2017.","false","Biography information for Liz Saville Roberts","Dwyfor Meirionnydd","Liz Saville Roberts","182273"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/992759","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-10-30","<p>This information is available in the published out of court disposals data tool: <a href="https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/733984/out-of-court-disposals-tool-2017-update.xlsx" target="_blank">https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/733984/out-of-court-disposals-tool-2017-update.xlsx</a></p><p> </p><p>To limit the data to Wales, filter the data using Police Force Area and select Dyfed-Powys, Gwent, North Wales and South Wales.</p><p> </p><p>For the number of Penalty Notices for Disorder (PND) issued for each tier of offence open the PND pivot table, limit the data to Wales, remove the variables from the rows box and drag the ‘Offence’ variable from the filters box into the rows box. For the total number of lower tier offences, in the ‘Offence’ filter, select all the offences that begin with DB. For the total number of higher tier offences, repeat as above, selecting all offences beginning with DA.</p><p> </p><p>For the proportion of people who paid their PND in full, open the PND pivot table, limit the data to Wales and ensure the ‘Outcomes’ variable is in the rows box. For each year, sum the numbers for ‘paid in full - timing unknown’ and divide this number by the total PNDs issued (grand total).</p><p> </p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart","182273","2018-10-30T17:38:46.137Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/992759/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/992759/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/992759/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-10-22","Fixed Penalties: Wales","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many and what proportion of people issued with a Penalty Notice for Disorder in Wales paid their fines in full in each year between 2013 and 2017.","false","Biography information for Liz Saville Roberts","Dwyfor Meirionnydd","Liz Saville Roberts","182274"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/992760","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-10-31","<p>Information on cautions is available in the published out of court disposals data tool: <a href="https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/733984/out-of-court-disposals-tool-2017-update.xlsx" target="_blank">https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/733984/out-of-court-disposals-tool-2017-update.xlsx</a></p><p> </p><p>To limit the data to Wales, filter the data using Police Force Area and select Dyfed-Powys, Gwent,</p><p>North Wales and South Wales.</p><p> </p><p>Open the Cautions pivot table and remove the variables from the rows box and drag the ‘Offence group’ variable from the filters box into the rows box.</p><p> </p><p>It is not possible to identify whether an offender received a simple or conditional caution as this data is not centrally held by the Ministry of Justice Court Proceedings Database.</p><p> </p><p>Summary motoring offences are mostly dealt with a Fixed Penalty Notice rather than a caution and as such are not included in the data.</p>","South East Cambridgeshire","Lucy Frazer",,"2018-10-31T15:01:36.877Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/992760/answer","Biography information for Lucy Frazer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/992760/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/992760/answer","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/992760/answer/previousversion/81945","Biography information for Rory Stewart","54","Justice","Justice","2018-10-22","Police Cautions: Wales","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many people were given a (a) simple and (b) conditional caution in Wales in each year between 2013 and 2017.","false","Biography information for Liz Saville Roberts","Dwyfor Meirionnydd","Liz Saville Roberts","182275"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/992761","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-10-31","<p>Information on cautions is available in the published out of court disposals data tool: <a href="https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/733984/out-of-court-disposals-tool-2017-update.xlsx" target="_blank">https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/733984/out-of-court-disposals-tool-2017-update.xlsx</a></p><p> </p><p>To limit the data to Wales, filter the data using Police Force Area and select Dyfed-Powys, Gwent,</p><p>North Wales and South Wales.</p><p> </p><p>Open the Cautions pivot table and remove the variables from the rows box and drag the ‘Offence group’ variable from the filters box into the rows box.</p><p> </p><p>It is not possible to identify whether an offender received a simple or conditional caution as this data is not centrally held by the Ministry of Justice Court Proceedings Database.</p><p> </p><p>Summary motoring offences are mostly dealt with a Fixed Penalty Notice rather than a caution and as such are not included in the data.</p>","South East Cambridgeshire","Lucy Frazer",,"2018-10-31T15:01:53.627Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/992761/answer","Biography information for Lucy Frazer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/992761/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/992761/answer","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/992761/answer/previousversion/81943","Biography information for Rory Stewart","54","Justice","Justice","2018-10-22","Police Cautions: Wales","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many cautions were issued in Wales as a result of (a) violence against a person or persons, (b) sexual offences, (c) robbery, (d) theft offences, (e) criminal damage and arson, (f) drug offences, (g) possession of a weapon or weapons, (h) public order offences, (i) miscellaneous crimes against society, (j) fraud offences, (k) summary offences involving motoring and (l) summary offences not involving motoring in each year between 2013 and 2017.","false","Biography information for Liz Saville Roberts","Dwyfor Meirionnydd","Liz Saville Roberts","182276"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/992762","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-10-31","<p>This data is published in the Court Outcomes by Police Force Area data tool: <a href="https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/733996/court-outcomes-by-pfa-2017-update.xlsx" target="_blank">https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/733996/court-outcomes-by-pfa-2017-update.xlsx</a></p>","South East Cambridgeshire","Lucy Frazer",,"2018-10-31T15:03:26.9Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/992762/answer","Biography information for Lucy Frazer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/992762/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/992762/answer","South East Cambridgeshire","Lucy Frazer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/992762/answer/previousversion/81947","Biography information for Lucy Frazer","54","Justice","Justice","2018-10-22","Prosecutions: Wales","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many people were prosecuted at magistrates’ courts in Wales for (a) violence against a person or persons, (b) sexual offences, (c) robbery, (d) theft offences, (e) criminal damage and arson, (f) drug offences, (g) possession of a weapon or weapons, (h) public order offences, (i) miscellaneous crimes against society, (j) fraud offences, (k) summary offences involving motoring, (l) summary offences not involving motoring and (m) indictable offences in each year between 2013 and 2017.","false","Biography information for Liz Saville Roberts","Dwyfor Meirionnydd","Liz Saville Roberts","182277"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/992763","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-10-31","<table><tbody><tr><td><p>This information is available in the published Court Outcomes by Police Force Area data tool: <a href="https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/733996/court-outcomes-by-pfa-2017-update.xlsx" target="_blank">https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/733996/court-outcomes-by-pfa-2017-update.xlsx</a> To limit the data to Wales, drag ‘Police Force Area’ field into the ‘Filters’ area and select Dyfed-Powys, Gwent, North Wales and South Wales. To see the number of prosecutions for triable either-way offences, drag the ‘Offence Type’ field into rows and sum the amounts for ’02: Triable Either Way’. For triable either way prosecutions at Crown Court, select ’01: Crown Court’ in the ‘Court Type’ filter. The data provided relates to the number of defendants convicted divided by the number of defendants proceeded against within a given year, provided as a conviction ratio. This gives a measure of the relative number of defendants who are found guilty within a given year for a certain offence, when compared with the number who are prosecuted that year for the same offence. All cases are first heard at Magistrates Court and more serious cases are sent for trial or sentencing at Crown Court, therefore some cases may be counted twice within a given year – once at Magistrates and then again at Crown Court.</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p>","South East Cambridgeshire","Lucy Frazer",,"2018-10-31T14:45:41.86Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/992763/answer","Biography information for Lucy Frazer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/992763/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/992763/answer","South East Cambridgeshire","Lucy Frazer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/992763/answer/previousversion/81912","Biography information for Lucy Frazer",